            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>In the archonship of Kipos son of Soios and Theodoros son of Mamos, on the 30th of Eumenideios. Resolved by the council. Since Teberios Klaudios son of Gaios of Antium (or Antiatas), having been appointed as supervisor for our city, has performed many great services to the state and has been a good man to the synoikismos of the city on every occasion; resolved that he and his children be proxenoi of the people of Entella, so that others also may know that our people is capable of rendering appropriate thanks to good men. The archons are to write this decree on a bronze plaque and exhibit it in the council chamber. Resolved by the assembly on the 4th Euerneios.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#JP">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The text of Lewis was at least partially based upon photographs taken pre-cleaning; and the initial texts of Nenci / Nenci and Asheri were derivative of Lewis' original transcription. The bibliography is intended to cover principal editions only. For a recent historical discussion, elucidating the First Punic War context, see Lombardo, Mario. 2018. «Entella tra i Cartaginesi e i Romani, ovvero da chi erano stati espulsi gli Entellini». In Munus Laetitiae. Studi miscellanei offerti a Maria Letizia Lazzarini, a cura di Francesco Camia, Lavinio Del Monaco, e Michela Nocita, 2:485–98. Rome: Sapienza Universita Editrice; and Souza 2024.<ref target="https://doi.org/10.13133/9788893770736">https://doi.org/10.13133/9788893770736</ref>. See also Souza 2024.</p>
                <p>The helmet depicted on the upper part of the tablet bears close similarity to those found on the relief moulded heads on several of the contemporary Latin rostra from the vicinity of the Egadi islands.</p>
             </div>
